Clea: Do you have any information about the fugitive Zagal?

Male Informant: I wonder if you were begged by the guards of
the Valier to know about that?

Male Informant: I have the information... but what's in it
for you if I tell you?
Thief Nora: C-Can't Valier be at peace...?

Male Informant: Hahaha, that guy is a masterpiece! We
information brokers aren't in the charity business, you
know.

Clea: Alright, I understand. I will negotiate, so everyone
please wait at the tavern.

Male Informant: It's better to negotiate with a smaller
group. Shall we begin?

Male Informant: To cut to the chase, I can't give you the
information.
Clea: Wasn't this supposed to be a negotiation?

Male Informant: The fugitive Zagal is a fellow professional.
If you let him escape, it will become troublesome for all of
you.
Clea: We will definitely catch him.

Male Informant: I heard that you can say anything if you're
just good with words... I've come up with a good idea...!

Male Informant: Information brokers rely on trust, and trust
comes with the readiness to endure pain.

Male Informant: Are you willing to do anything to complete
the mission?

Clea: W-Why are you suddenly showing me that...! Please put
your pants back on quickly!

Male Informant: I said that you can say anything if you're
just good with words, didn't I? Are you willing to prove
your determination with your own 'words'?

Male Informant: That's a good judgment. You're suited to be
an informant.
Would you like to skip the adult scene?

Clea: I kept my promise. Now it's your turn to answer with
trust.

Male Informant: I've heard that the fugitive Zagal has fled
to the Golden Highway in the Oros region, seeking refuge
with the Pegal Bandit Gang.

Male Informant: It would be more convenient for us if Zagal
disappeared as well.
Clea: So you were planning to tell me from the beginning...!

Male Informant: Haha, I like strong-willed women, so I'm
expecting great things from you when I give you this
request.
Male Informant: Because I trust you.

Male Informant: That's right, you have to do it! A beauty
like you is a rare opponent--
Male Informant: W-What are you doing!

Clea: I believe that trust comes with the willingness to
endure pain. I would like to see an example of that first.

Male Informant: I-I understand. I intend to acknowledge that
you are skilled.
